mkdir /data  --->>> create directory 

mount /dev/nvme1n1 /data   --->> mount the volume to that direcoty which is created preveoius commnd

ls -la  check the files in the direcotry 

mkfs.xfs -f /dev/nvme1n1  ---> these commnd is formating the volume 

lsblk -o +SERIAL  --->> it shows the which vloume is attached with use of volume id 

https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/ebs-using-volumes.html


